article.headline: Mississippi 57, Arkansas St. 45
article.story: OXFORD, Miss. -- David Huertas scored 24 points, including 18 in the second half to lift Mississippi to a 65-52 win over Arkansas State on Friday night in the season opener for both schools. Huertas was 8-of-11 from the field and added six rebounds and two assists. Preseason All-SEC point guard Chris Warren added 14 points, but missed on his opening 11 shots from the field. The loss spoiled John Brady's debut as head coach at Arkansas State. Shawn Morgan led the Red Wolves (0-1) with13 points. Arkansas State led 27-24 at halftime after leading early by as many as seven points. Huertas opened the second half with eight consecutive points, giving the Rebels a 32-29 lead with 16:46 left. Ole Miss built their biggest lead, 55-41, on a three-point shot by Huertas with 853 left. The Red Wolves never got closer than nine points again.
